message.content: {"reasoning":"Ground truth: a helicopter is airborne even though its rotor blades are motionless; a character stands underneath it. Core issue: helicopter’s visual/animation is frozen (rotor not spinning) while game logic still treats it as flying; character is present below.\nGenerated report: describes a helicopter extraction scene where both helicopter and the figure below are frozen in mid-air without expected movement, creating an unrealistic effect. This likewise points to helicopter animation being frozen while it remains aloft, and mentions the character under/suspended from it.\nBoth reports point to the same phenomenon: airborne helicopter appears static (no rotor/animation) with a stationary character beneath, indicating the same underlying animation freeze bug. Minor wording differences (motionless rotor vs entire helicopter/frozen figure) do not signify a different issue.","match":true}

The generated report concerns visual rendering of lighting and shadows at night—helicopter appears as a black silhouette with no detail. No mention of rotor animation, hovering behavior, or character oscillation. Likewise, the ground truth does not mention lighting or shadow problems. Therefore they describe different bugs.","match":false}

It is described as static, not rotating or moving away, and the problem is that it is rendered in screen space, not that it is floating/rotating in world space.\nThe symptoms (static screen-space object) and the object type (UFO vs car) differ from the ground-truth symptoms (floating, rotating, moving world-space car). Therefore they do not describe the same bug.","match":false}

There is no mention of the boat being physically propelled by the player or any movement anomaly; likewise, the ground truth does not mention transparency or clipping. Therefore, they refer to different bugs.","match":false}
